---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Methodology" description="Methodology for provenance, maturity dimensions, and phased growth of the Digital Public Infrastructure Ecosystem Atlas." currentPage="/methodology/">
  <div class="container" style="padding-top: var(--space-10); padding-bottom: var(--space-16); max-width: 960px;">
    <h1 style="margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">Methodology</h1>
    <p style="font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-8); max-width: 72ch;">
      The Atlas treats governance, stewardship, interoperability, accessibility, sustainability, and procurement readiness
      as first-class dimensions. It is intentionally not a popularity ranking or a software catalog.
    </p>

    <section aria-labelledby="phase-heading" style="margin-bottom: var(--space-10);">
      <h2 id="phase-heading" style="margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">Phased Implementation</h2>
      <ol style="padding-left: var(--space-6); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-3);">
        <li><strong>Phase 1:</strong> Curated cohort, provenance, profile pages, accessible tables, and basic map/graph views.</li>
        <li><strong>Phase 2:</strong> GitHub, DPG, GovStack, OpenSSF, and publiccode.yml enrichment with monthly automation.</li>
        <li><strong>Phase 3:</strong> Relationship intelligence across standards, funders, conferences, deployments, and organizations.</li>
        <li><strong>Phase 4:</strong> Optional private overlays for meetings, introductions, and collaboration notes.</li>
        <li><strong>Phase 5:</strong> Large-scale ecosystem expansion across DPGs, GovStack building blocks, civic tech, and standards ecosystems.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="provenance-heading" style="margin-bottom: var(--space-10);">
      <h2 id="provenance-heading" style="margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">Provenance and Confidence</h2>
      <p>
        Important facts are stored with provenance metadata. The data model distinguishes manual curation, declared facts,
        inferred relationships, and scraped or API-derived fields. Confidence levels make uncertainty explicit rather than hidden.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="maturity-heading" style="margin-bottom: var(--space-10);">
      <h2 id="maturity-heading" style="margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">Maturity Dimensions</h2>
      <p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-4); max-width: 72ch; color: var(--color-text-muted);">
        The Atlas is being built along the maturity-model approach described in <code>2510.04603v1</code>.
        We use that framework to guide what evidence we collect, how we structure confidence and provenance,
        and how we phase the product roadmap.
      </p>
      <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
        <table class="data-table" aria-label="Maturity dimensions">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th scope="col">Dimension</th>
              <th scope="col">Why it matters</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><th scope="row">Code</th><td>Commit history, contributors, and release engineering indicate maintenance capacity.</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row">Governance</th><td>Transparent decision-making and policy clarity support institutional trust.</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row">Stewardship</th><td>Long-term custodianship matters for public-interest adoption and resilience.</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row">Public-sector</th><td>Known government deployments and implementation evidence indicate operational maturity.</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row">Accessibility</th><td>Public infrastructure must work for disabled people and low-friction procurement contexts.</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row">Sustainability</th><td>Funding resilience and maintainer capacity affect whether a project can endure.</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row">Security</th><td>Policies, disclosures, and dependency health reduce operational risk.</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row">Interoperability</th><td>Standards and APIs determine whether systems can cooperate over time.</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row">Procurement</th><td>Support ecosystems and documentation influence public-sector adoption.</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row">Community</th><td>Contributor health and issue response show whether participation is viable.</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row">Documentation</th><td>Onboarding and operational docs are essential for implementers and procurement teams.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>